        <p>When is the #FRUP a #MRUP? When it&#8217;s summer and someone takes a Friday off work. </p>

<p>I hear it&#8217;s summer in many parts of the Country. I say &#8220;I hear&#8221; because in Seattle we&#8217;re still waiting for summer to arrive. While we wait and continue working without all that distracting fun-in-the-sun, here is the newest Round Up Post. (Want something featured? <a href="http://expressionengine.com/forums/viewthread/192661/">The best way is to let me know.</a>)</p>

<p><strong>Add-Ons</strong><br />
<a href="http://devot-ee.com/add-ons/google-custom-search/">Google Custom Search</a> now available from Amphibian Design.</p>

<p>Solspace Facebook <a href="http://solsp.ac/e8od">Connect 2.0</a> released. New API, easier to use, and now supports several social plugins </p>

<p><a href="http://www.devdemon.com/channel_images/">Channel Images 5</a> gets a complete new design and bunch of new features.</p>

<p>Stephen Lewis released Crumbly, a new EE2 module which makes adding breadcrumbs to your website super-easy. <a href="http://experienceinternet.co.uk/software/crumbly/">Full details are here</a>, along with a <a href="http://experienceinternet.co.uk/blog/introducing-crumbly">background blog post here</a>.</p>

<p>“<a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/expressionengine-detector/">ExpressionEngine Detector</a>” Firefox Addon also got officially approved by mozilla.</p>

<p><a href="http://experienceinternet.co.uk/software/testee/">Testee</a> is released for unit testing and TDD for ExpressionEngine addons.</p>

<p><strong>Articles</strong><br />
Focus Lab writes an article about <a href="http://focuslabllc.com/blog/utilizing-the-template-debugger-in-expressionengine-add-ons">helping developers debug templates</a>.</p>

<p>A new series of posts on Integrating ExpressionEngine with Third-Party APIs. <a href="http://experienceinternet.co.uk/blog/integrating-ee-with-apis-1-of-4">Part one is here</a>, <a href="http://bit.ly/kiIBvx">Part two is here</a>.</p>

<p><strong>Videos</strong></p>

<p>Ryan Irelan now has a <a href="http://mijingo.com/products/screencasts/upgrading-expressionengine/">free video on Upgrading ExpressionEngine</a>. With the release of EE 2.2 it’s important that everyone knows how to properly plan, perform and test an EE upgrade.</p>

<p>And Brad, from Dev Demon, created a <a href="http://www.devdemon.com/blog/how_to_make_quick_jquery_gallery_with_channel_images_5_in_expressionengine/">seventeen minute long video tutorial on how to make a jQuery Gallery with Channel Images</a>.</p>

<p><br />
<strong>Events</strong><br />
<a href="http://www.creat-ee.com/classes/more/introduction_to_expressionengine_20/">Intro to ExpressionEngine Two</a> free seminar on June 30, 2pm - 3pm EST by Create-EE.</p>

<p><strong>Announcements from the Community</strong><br />
<a href="http://seesparkbox.com/">Spark Box</a>, an ExpressionEngine website, gets featured in NetMag in July! Congrats!</p>

<p>From Ryan, &#8220;<a href="http://ee-spotlight.com">EE Spotlight</a> is a source for ExpressionEngine Tips, Tutorials, Reviews, and News.&nbsp; The aim is to not only be a source of information, but more importantly an easy place for others to post articles of their own, creating links back to their own site in the author bio, and increasing the networking within the community.&nbsp; Dare I say it, but almost a NetTuts+ type of site focused on ExpressionEngine. And now, EE Spotlight is running an AppleTV giveaway for anyone who submits an ExpressionEngine-related review before July 15th. <a href="http://ee-spotlight.com/news/write_a_review_for_ee_spotlight_win_an_apple_tv">More info here</a>. </p>

